section.appfeatures.hidden-xs
  .container
    .row
      .col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1
        h2.center Gain More Control, Manage Your Asthma Worries
        p.center AsthmaSense Cloud helps you make quality decisions to improve your asthma risk, keep your asthma well-controlled and give your healthcare provider data to make adjustments to your asthma treatment plan.
    .row
      .col-sm-3.col-sm-offset-1
        .feat-item
          h4 Personal asthma management
          p Set your medications, triggers, symptoms, visualise data and get insights just for you.
        .feat-item
          h4 Record asthma symptoms, easily.
          p No one has the room to carry around a pad of paper and pen. The simplicity and ease of logging symptoms and triggers as they occur, wheeze and peak flow measurements, scheduled medication and unscheduled medication use can be logged with a few quick taps.
        .feat-item-wrap
          h3 Coming soon
          .feat-item
            h4 Weather with a purpose
            p Keep a heads up on the weather to better prepare you for your day. Know if the pollen count is high that day or if dark skies are moving in so you can better manage your asthma.
      .col-sm-4
        img.center.img-responsive(src="/assets/img/iPhoneCloud.png", alt="iPhoneCloud")

      .col-sm-3.right
        .feat-item
          h4 Get more from your doctor’s visits
          p AsthmaSense Cloud removes the guesswork from treatment adherence, triggers and symptoms. Don’t waste an hour at the doctor trying to remember everything from the previous month, let AsthmaSense help.	
        .feat-item
          h4 Emergency info, with one tap.
          p Asthma attacks are scary, especially if you are alone. Simply tap your emergency contact in AsthmaSense and help is on the way.
        .feat-item-wrap
          h3 Coming Soon
          .feat-item
            h4 Location, location, location
            p Where you are plays a part in your asthma risk. Through a neural network and GPS, know where asthma attacks are happening or when people are experiencing high WheezeRATEs or increase in symptoms.	

